						               													<description>BigBalls represents an advanced development of EinStein w&amp;#195;&amp;#188;rfelt nicht! and consists of similarly short rules. The neutral balls however do not allow to use the same successful strategies as in EinStein w&amp;#195;&amp;#188;rfelt nicht!.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The wooden gameboard is triangular with 28 fields.&amp;#10;Each player gets a color (black or white) with six stones each. In addition there are six neutral marbles, called Big Balls in the third corner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When it's your turn you may roll a dice and move an according numbered stone of yours upwards or sideways or you move one of the BigBalls downwards.&amp;#10;You may beat (eliminate) own stones as this enables you to move faster. But this also bears the risk running out of stones that will cause losing the game.&amp;#10;Winner of the game is the player who reaches first the corner of the BigBalls with one of his own stones.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
